news.title: Sunshine 100 China Holdings defaults on $170 million bond
news.para: Sunshine 100 said in an exchange filing that it was not able to repay the principal and interest of a 10.5% bond due Dec 5, "owing to liquidity issues arising from the adverse impact of a number of factors including the macroeconomic environment and the real estate industry."

news.title: Evergrande moves toward restructuring; state swoops in to contain risk
news.para: Evergrande which is grappling with over $300 billion in liabilities and is at risk of becoming China's biggest ever default, said on Monday that the committee included officials from state entities and would play an important role in "mitigating and eliminating the future risks" of the group.

news.title: Israeli firm to sell HSBC Tower in New York for $855 million
news.para: The Israeli company, which is 63% owned by Discount Investment Corp, said it had also sold property in Israel for 390 million shekels ($123 million).

news.title: HC seeks ED response on bail plea by Ambience group's promoter
news.para: The ED had raided Gehlot, his company Aman Hospitality Private Limited (AHPL), some other firms of the Ambience group, director in the company Dayanand Singh, Mohan Singh Gehlot, and their associates in July last year.

news.title: Hong Kong: New World Development to offer 300 homes at 50% discount to market price
news.para: Once the proposal was approved by the government, New World would build 300 one- to three-bedroom flats ranging in size from 300 to 550 square feet in the New Territories West district.

news.title: Saint-Gobain buys U.S.-based GCP for around $2.3 billion
news.para: "This acquisition is a decisive step in establishing Saint-Gobain's leading position worldwide in construction chemicals with total sales of more than 4 billion euros ($4.51 billion), up from 3 billion euros," Saint-Gobain said in a statement.

news.title: Aparna Enterprises invests Rs 100 crore in its tiles division
news.para: Aparna Enterprises is also aligning their resources to expand their dealer network and their market presence. In FY21 the company had increased their network in India by 23% and this year they plan to further boost it by 30%.

news.title: Shriram Properties sets IPO price band at Rs 113-118 per share
news.para: Shriram Properties has reduced its offer for sale size to Rs 350 crore from Rs 550 crore earlier. Now, the IPO size will be Rs 600 crore against Rs 800 crore earlier.

news.title: Nagpur improvement trust demands market rate for 32 acres land for smart city project
news.para: In violation of the state government’s decision, NIT has decided to adjust the cost of the land in its share of Rs 250 crore to be disbursed to the civic body for the Smart City Project.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: More takers for OTS scheme as awareness drives pay off
news.para: For several years, successive state governments had given houses under various schemes to beneficiaries. But these houses are not entitled for transfer of title. Similarly, many people living in these flats shoulder the burden of paying back installments.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder arrested for duping five flat buyers of Rs 10 crore
news.para: Shah was arrested on charges of cheating, forgery, breach of trust and under Maharashtra Ownership of Flats. Shah has been sent to police custody.

news.title: Aravalis: Activist approaches SC on illegal farmhouses
news.para: The Supreme Court had earlier this year ordered the demolition of all structures in Khori village, a settlement in Faridabad that came up over several years on by encroaching on protected Aravali land.

news.title: DDA officials meet residents in outer Delhi village on land pooling policy
news.para: To address the problem of housing, the DDA has prepared the land pooling policy with the aim to acquire land from owners living in rural areas of the national capital, according to an official statement.

news.title: Evergrande shares hit 11-year low after firm says no guarantee it can meet repayments
news.para: Evergrande, once China's top-selling developer, is grappling with more than $300 billion in liabilities. A collapse could send shockwaves through the country's property sector and beyond.

news.title: Builders' body moves SC against construction ban in Delhi-NCR
news.para: "It is submitted that the present blanket ban on all construction activities takes within its sweep even small constructions of residential and other units, which can in no manner be said to be causing large-scale pollution," the plea said.
